@node "Intro" "What does NetBar and NetView do then ?"

@{b}------------------------------------------------------------------------
                              Introduction
------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

NetBar version 6.0 is a compact button bar for launching net applications
but has a couple tricks up it's sleaves. (see @{"overview" link "overview" 0} for more details)

It can also start your Log On and Hang Up scripts and with the help of
NetView unarchive most common archiving formats (even DOS and UNIX) as
well as View and Play most files found on the Net see @{"Requirements" link "Require" 0} for details.

NetView is also a stand alone prog so you can use it to uncompress
and view files without starting NetBar. (see @{"NetView" link "netview" 0} for more details)

Both NetBar and NetView use and rely on Gui4Cli by D.Keletsekis (c)
You can find the latest version on aminet/dev/gui4cli.lha, at the time
of writing it was on version 2.2. (see @{"Gui4Cli" link "gui4cli" 0} for more of what it can do)

D.Keletsekis is godsend and if you find either of my progs of use please
register Gui4Cli it's very cheap and you can make prog's like this with
little or no knowledge of programing.

Please read the @{"License" link "Lic" 0} for Gui4Cli for details of registration etc.

**** Gui4Cli WWW Page is now at http://users.hol.gr/~dck/gcmain.htm ****


@endnode


