@node "install" "Installing NetBar etc"

@{b}Make sure Gui4Cli v2.2 is already installed and rebooted to set the assign for Guis:
or the NetBar instalation will not work.@{ub}

All the installer does is copy a small script file to C: for use with xanim, so if
you don't intend to use xanim (see @{"Helpers" link "helpers" 0}) forget the install icon.  

Just put the NetBar drawer anywhere you want then click the Install icon.

You can move the drawer again at any time as NetBar will always find it.

Now start Netbar with it's icon and a large gui will launch (only if first time)
this is where you will set the paths to your Net app's. You can type them in
or use the get buttons for each app (easier) to browse your system.

Once done press save and it will exit.

Now select Misc from the menu to set up your dialler scripts (if needed) and set
your UnArc drawer (where you want any files to be extracted/decoded) then press
save as above to finish.
 
 
@{b}That's it !!@{ub}

See @{"Overview" link "overview" 0} for what each button and menu item does and etc.

@endnode


@node "probs" "Help !!! I`m loosing hair here "

@{b}"Standard unexpanded 68000 owners (A500, A600 etc) hard luck if this don`t
 work as your holding the rest of us back."@{ub}


@{b}Below are a few Q+A's of common problems:@{ub}

@{i}Before you continue have you read all the docs/guides etc for relevant
programs ??@{ui}

@{b}Installing NetBar:@{ub}

Q  I try to install NetBar, but a requester says something like
   "Guis: not found" or "C:gui not found" and it won`t install.

A  You have not installed Gui4Cli and rebooted your system before you
   installed NetBar (see @{"Installing NetBar" link "install" 0}.

Q  Gui4Cli is installed and rebooted, but NetBar still won`t install.

A  Check your OS version. Gui4Cli needs OS 2.04 or above to run so
   NetBar will not install or run if lower.


@{b}Running NetBar:@{ub}

Q  NetBar looks really kak with some dodgey colours.

A  NetBar uses the Magic Workbench colour scheme. Just click the "ClickMe"
   icon and (as if by magic) NetBar will look right. You will still have
   to start Palette Prefs to save the new palette or it will be lost after
   reboot. (you must be running 8 or more colours)

Q  The text in NetView etc is mis-sized etc.

A  You don`t have times.font in your Fonts drawer. This is the standard
   one that comes with WorkBench 2.04 and above. Just copy it from your
   Fonts disk to WorkBench/Fonts.

   @{b}TIP!@{ub} If you want to change the font in NetView etc, remove
   times.font and rename your chosen font to times.font, but follow this:-

   Font must be able to show 11 and 13 sizes.
   Font must be bitmapped
   (remember a font consists of a drawer of the same name)

Q  I can`t set the paths my Net App`s etc, when I press the get button
   I just get an error.

A  You don`t have the asl.library installed (found on cover disks/Aminet)
   NetBar and Gui4Cli use this library for file requester etc.

Q  All ok and NetBar installed but I can`t access the help from the menu.

A  You need AmigaGuide in your C: drawer (or multiview renamed in C:) as 
   NetBar needs it to run it`s guide file. Just copy it there and all will
   be ok. I ask for it in C: because some versions of WorkBench put in
   different places and makes it hard to account for.
   You don`t have to do this but you will have to click the guide for help.

Q  I have NetBar setup and running like a dream, but my logon scripts etc 
   won`t work.

A  If your scripts are Arexx ones (most are) you must make Dos script and
   icon to launch them.

   i.e. ;Bobs dialler script
        rx AmiTCP:bin/logon.rexx

        And make a @{b}project@{ub} icon with a default tool of IconX and
        select this in the Log On bit of the Misc gui (from NetBar menu)
        Make sure rx is in your path (S: is the norm)
        Check the icon flags for script and executable are checked.
   
@{b}If you don`t understand any of the above get someone who does@{ub}

Q  After running NetBar I wished to use one of my Arexx progs, but when I 
   start RexxMast it says it`s already running.

A  NetBar automatically looks for RexxMast in WorkBench:System/ and if found
   it starts it so as to be ready for any Log On scripts AWeb helpers etc. 
   If RexxMast is already running NetBar will not try to load it.
   Once you have learnt a bit about Gui4Cli you could remove it to save
   memory. I only put it there so you don`t have to put it in WBStartup or
   what ever so it is only loaded when needed. (saves memory)


@{b}NetView/AutoView/AutoIcon:@{ub}


Q  I can`t view, unarc, play certain filetypes (avi`s, jpeg`s zip`s etc).

A  1) You don`t have the correct helper installed (see @{"Helpers" link "helpers" 0}
   2) Your system is the wrong spec for the helper (see docs with helper)
   3) It`s a filetype I have not accounted for. ("I tried my best")
      (no Mac filetypes supported as ShapeShifter is best for this)

Q  I loaded a filetype and found it to be a program, so I ran it with 
   NetView. The program made my system crash or corrupt.

A  Sorry but you were warned enough times that this could happen.

Q  Fli/flc, avi and qt movies etc run really slow and jerky.

A  Sorry but I used xanim as the helper for these as it was all in one to
   save installing loads of helpers for each filetype. (better ones can be
   found on Aminet) You also need a powerful machine to view non-Amiga
   movies/animation types.

@{b}Pakit:@{ub}

Q  When I use lha or lha-mime etc, lha starts compressing everything in my
   drawer.

A  You did not click a file(s) in the file selector so lha thinks you want
   everything compressed (see @{"Pakit" link "pakit" 0}) Using wildcards as the filename
   (i.e. #? on it's own instead of myfile.#? or #?.doc) has the same effect.

Q  I picked my file(s) but lha still goes bananas.

A  You may have typed the filename in the file window and got it wrong
   and this will confuse lha etc.

@{b}Misc:@{ub}

Q  How can I change the way NetBar etc looks and works.

A  Easy, learn Gui4Cli (read the guide) and you can edit to your hearts
   content. (please do not make a little alteration then call it yours as
   I have spent a while on it and deserve some credit)

Q  When I try to select a path/file in the ASL requesters or type them in
   the windows. I find that they get cropped or just won`t function.

A  You are exceeding the buffer (100 characters each) and the end will be
   cut off. Don't worry the file(s) are still there, just you can't see them.

Q  Why all the buttons in NetView and Pakit?, Why not a cycler gadget?

A  I can`t stand starting up a program and then having to wade through
   cyclers only to find the selection I want is the last one, so I used
   lots of buttons to make them quicker to use.


